The DA briefs the media on the state of governance in a selection of DA-run municipalities, three years since the 2016 municipal election. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. CAPE TOWN - The Democratic Alliance briefed the media on the state of governance in a selection of DA-run municipalities, three years since the 2016 municipal elections. READ: EFF cut ties with DA This week marks three years since South Africans entrusted the DA with governing more than 30 municipalities across the country. Among these are the Midvaal in Gauteng and Kouga in the Eastern Cape.